Filmmaker Michael König from Cologne has created an amazing video showing solar activity . 
  It was made by stitching together footage from Nasa’s Solar Dynamics Observatory over five years . 
  The footage includes plasma raining down on the sun, an extreme solar eruption and even a comet breezing through the sun . 
  The movie was created by using footage recorded by the Nasa spacecraft between 2011 and 2015 . 
 